  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This research study is testing the &quot;chemo-switch&quot; strategy in melanoma, using biochemotherapy
      initially to shrink tumors and then switching to daily low-dose chemotherapy (temozolomide)
      together with sorafenib. The purpose of this study is to find out what effects (good and bad)
      biochemotherapy followed by temozolomide plus sorafenib have on melanoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
